  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 17 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The expression for electric potential energy of an isolated point charge Q at a distance r relative to infinity is given as",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\(V = ∫^B_A E.dl\\)",
        "\\(V = -q_0 ∫^B_A E.dl\\)",
        "\\(V = Q / 4π∈_0 r\\)",
        "\\(V = Q / 4π∈_0 r²\\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(V = Q / 4π∈_0 r\\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Electric Potential vs. Potential Energy</h3><p>The <strong>electric potential</strong> (V) due to a point charge is:</p><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'><strong>V = kQ/r = Q/(4π∈<sub>0</sub>r)</strong></p><h4 style='color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 15px;'>Distinctions:</h4><table style='width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;'><tr><th style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; background: #f2f2f2;'>Option</th><th style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; background: #f2f2f2;'>Description</th></tr><tr><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'>∫E·dl</td><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'>General potential difference definition</td></tr><tr><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'>-q<sub>0</sub>∫E·dl</td><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'>Work done on test charge</td></tr><tr><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; background: #e8f5e9;'>Q/(4π∈<sub>0</sub>r)</td><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; background: #e8f5e9;'><strong>Correct potential formula</strong></td></tr><tr><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'>Q/(4π∈<sub>0</sub>r²)</td><td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'>Electric field (E), not potential</td></tr></table></div>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electric Potential",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Electric Charges",
      "Work"
    ]
  },
